### Welcome to Source Code Pro.

Source Code Pro is a set of OpenType fonts that have been designed to work well in user interface (UI) environments. In addition to a functional OpenType font, this open source project provides all of the source files that were used to build this OpenType font by using the AFDKO makeotf tool.

### Get the Code 
https://github.com/adobe/Source-Code-Pro

### See some Examples

The following are live examples rendered using the Adobe [Edge Web Fonts Collection](http://www.edgefonts.com/).

An example showing the HTML embed usage.

``` javascript
(function( $ ){

  $.fn.maxHeight = function() {
  
    var max = 0;

    this.each(function() {
      max = Math.max( max, $(this).height() );
    });

    return max;
  };
})( jQuery );
```

And another in Ruby ... 
``` ruby
def multiply(a,b)
  product = a * b
  return product
end
```

And how to use the Source Code Pro as a web font! 
``` html
<script src="http://use.edgefonts.net/source-code-pro.js"></script>
```   

``` html
<style type="text/css">
code {
  width: 100%;
  color: #222;
  background-color: #fff;

  font-family: source-code-pro, Monaco, "Bitstream Vera Sans Mono", "Lucida Console", Terminal, monospace;
  font-size: 14px;

  border-radius: 2px;
  -moz-border-radius: 2px;
  -webkit-border-radius: 2px;
}
</style>

```

### Web Font Usage

Source Code Pro is available as a web font from the Adobe [Edge Web Fonts Collection](http://www.edgefonts.com/).
